        "title": "How do you set crossContext and enptySessionPath in Jboss7?",
        "body": "<p>I am trying to migrate the deployment of some applications from tomcat 6 to jboss-as 7.<\/p>\n\n<p>A single sign-on mechanism has been implemented for these projects, which, in order to work, needs to have crossContext=\"true\" set in the tomcat context.xml file and emptySessionPath=\"true\" in the connector configuration found within server.xml. <\/p>\n\n<p>How can these settings be mimicked in jboss7? I know that jboss uses a modified tomcat as a servlet container, but I have been unable to find any of these settings.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 8604889,
